        <h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <h3 id="whats-a-good-link-velocity">What's a good link velocity?</h3>
        <p>There's no universal number. Compare your growth rate to competitors in your niche. A healthy pattern is gradual, consistent growth that roughly correlates with your content output and marketing activities.</p>
        <h3 id="can-you-build-links-too-fast">Can you build links too fast?</h3>
        <p>Yes. If the links are low-quality or obviously artificial. But a genuine viral moment earning hundreds of quality links quickly won't hurt you. Google can tell the difference between a news article blowing up and a link spam campaign.</p>
        <h3 id="does-losing-links-affect-velocity">Does losing links affect velocity?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Negative link velocity. Losing more links than you gain. Can signal declining relevance. Monitor lost links regularly and use <a href="/glossary/link-reclamation/">link reclamation</a> to recover important ones.</p>
